 livestream  During the ceremony  the regimental commanding officer and the company cadet captains introduce themselves and Gen  J H  Binford Peay III  62  VMI superintendent  addresses the new cadets and their parents  The ceremony   and the video stream   ends with the new cadets marching in formation out of Cameron Hall  Their next stop is barracks and the beginning of their training  DVDs of the ceremony will also be available for purchase in the VMI Video Store   VMI  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 